r=f(\theta)
(h,k)
r=1+\cos^2(2\theta)
x = r\cos\theta = \cos\theta(1+\cos^2(2\theta))
y = r\sin\theta = \sin\theta(1+\cos^2(2\theta))
(1,1)
x = 1+ \cos\theta(1+\cos^2(2\theta))
y = 1+ \sin\theta(1+\cos^2(2\theta))
r>0
\sqrt{r^2}=r
r = \sqrt{x^2+y^2} = \sqrt{(1+ \cos\theta(1+\cos^2(2\theta)))^2 + (1+ \sin\theta(1+\cos^2(2\theta)))^2}
